place.name: PRESTONKIRK
place.gazetteerText: Prestonkirk, par., Haddingtonshire, on river Tyne, 5½ miles W. of Dunbar, 7058 ac., pop. 1929; P.O., T.O., called Prestonkirk or East Linton. See LINTON, EAST. (In 1887, John Bartholomew's Gazetteer of the British Isles)
